{
  "stem": "4284.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A luxury, and I do mean a luxury, was when you could go to the German kitchen and get the, the coffee-- what do you call it?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What's left over from coffee-- coffee grind.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because they did not use regular coffee.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They used ersatz coffee, which was mostly roasted barley which was still at least hopefully of some nutritional value.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And you'd make, not hamburgers, but patties.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, you'd make patties like hamburger out of this.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And eating this and eliminating it was not a joy.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But you tried everything and anything to get some nutritional value.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were there till 1944 when my mother and I were supposedly given the privilege of staying behind to bring in the harvest.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, from 1940-- I'm sorry '43, not '44-- we were supposed to have the identification card, an identification badge, that would allow us to stay behind.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, what happened was that during the time that we were in this ghetto, you had this tremendous, tremendous fear that you would be caught in a raid.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, raids were the standard way of slowly cleaning, clearing out the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You lived in a apartment building sort of a structure.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you had a periodic raid where the street was cordoned off-- always at night, always a German shepherd, always with a searchlight, always with sticks and bayonets, even.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they would come into the room and clear it out, chase you down the staircase, if there was one, onto the trucks for a destination, again, unknown.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We happened to live in a place that had sort of an attic, at least the-- underneath the roof, which had to hold up the roof some major beams.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the door would open up to our room.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
